    "updated_at": "2013-07-11T00:43:02Z",
    "body": "Another additional lint would be warning about enums where some variants are much larger than others, since the size of the whole enum is the size of the largest variant and so variants with very different sizes waste space. (It could suggest it be broken out and placed behind an `~`.) E.g.\n\n``` rust\nenum Foo { // \"warning: mismatched variant sizes\"\n   A,\n   B(int, int, int, int, int, int, int, int) // \"note: this variant is much larger than the others\"\n}\n\n// could become\n\nstruct BInner(int, int, int, int, int, int, int, int);\nenum Foo {\n   A,\n   B(~BInner)\n}\n```\n\n(This one should probably be allow by default.)\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
