    "updated_at": "2014-07-29T03:04:21Z",
    "body": "There is now a `variant-size-difference` lint which does this just for enum variants. I am not sure this in particular belongs in rustc, especially now that we have loadable lints. The problem is, \"how big is too big?\".\n\nI agree this is nice. But it belongs in a separate analysis tool, not rustc. Anyone object to closing?\n",
